{
    "title": "Where did the phrase 'be the bigger person' come from? - Quora",
    "tags": [],
    "response": [
        {
            "author_info": {
                "name": "Garrick Saito",
                "href": "/profile/Garrick-Saito"
            },
            "answer_text": "I'm not sure if the exact origin is known, but if you think about the words, I think it'll lead you to the answer. The bigger man has nothing to prove.  He looks like a fool trying to defeat the smaller, weaker man.  It is obvious, he doesn't need to.  He takes the moral high road, sometimes allowing the smaller man to believe he has won (when everyone knows he hasn't).   ",
